cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with optimizing the performance of randomized algorithms. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves decision-making based on observed features. Additionally, since the experiments involve hyperparameter tuning for image classification tasks, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Bayesian priors suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the optimization aspect could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
